ng as I write, I will never be lost.\n\n- Nikki\n|\nStop chasing people who keep running away from your presence, because even if you succeed in catching them, sooner or later they would run away.\n\n- Unknown\n|\nI have a definition of success. For me, it's very simple. It's not about wealth and fame and power. It's about how many shining eyes I have around me.\n\n- Benjamin\n|\nChristmas is like candy; it slowly melts in your mouth sweetening every taste bud, making you wish it could last forever.\n\n- Richelle E. Goodrich, Smile Anyway\n|\nDo not instigate or treat any of your employees, working at your place, with contempt. Treat everyone with respect. You never know what benefit a person will bring.\n\n- Dada\n|\nBy the grace of God, I will finish what I have started.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nThere can be no friendship without confidence, and no confidence without integrity.\n\n- Samuel\n|\nPeople are so stupid. They think they've got the whole puzzle figured out, but they're really so far off.\n\n- Laurie Faria Stolarz, Deadly Little Games\n|\nFor desired conclusions, we ask ourselves, 'Can I believe this?', but for unpalatable conclusions we ask, 'Must I believe this?\n\n- Thomas Gilovich, How We Know What Isn't So: The Fallibility of Human Reason in Everyday Life\n|\nShe leaves, carrying a biodegradable carrier bag that reads THE SUICIDE SHOP on one side, and on the other: HAS YOUR LIFE BEEN A FAILURE? LET’S MAKE YOUR DEATH A SUCCESS!\n\n- Jean Teulé, The Suicide Shop\n|\n...CompuServe, and it was not sophisticated, guys. It was the cave painting equivalent to Tumblr.\n\n- Felicia Day, You're Never Weird on the Internet\n|\nThe, per second great thought investment will yield the best hourly harvest of great life.\n\n- Ernest Agyemang Yeboah, The Untapped Wonderer in You: Dare to Do the Undone\n|\nIn life, never talk about problems. Talk about solutions.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nTo change the world, see the world through your heart, world will change along with your percepti